            "title": "Kryfo",
            "date": "2021",
            "description": [
                "\"Kryfo\" is the first album by Antonis Leontidis. It includes mostly his own compositions and some old Cretan tunes, with mantinades (traditional rhyming couplets) from the collection \"Cretan Mantinades\" (1933) by the notable folklorist Maria Lioudaki.",
                "His personal compositions are inspired by the landscape of Cretan music, and in combination with traditional lyrics and Cretan dance melodies, they form the album’s content. They are performed by the duet of lyra and laouto, played by Antonis Leontidis and Giannis Linardakis."
